label.value: normal protein localization to cell cortex of cell tip during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cell cortex of the cell tip is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to microtubule plus-end

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the plus ends end of microtubules is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein level in Arp2/3 complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured in the Arp2/3 protein complex is lower than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased ATP binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of ATP binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: increased double-strand break repair via single-strand annealing

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of double-strand break repair via single-strand annealing is increased.

label.value: increased 3' overhang single-stranded DNA endodeoxyribonuclease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of 3' overhang single-stranded DNA endodeoxyribonuclease activity is increased.

label.value: excess nuclear envelope present during mitotic interphase

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain more nuclear envelope than normal during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Excess nuclear envelopes may take the form of intranuclear membrane stacks or invaginations, or small cytoplasmic spheres that are attached to the nucleus, have double lipid bilayer membranes, and may contain structures resembling nuclear pores.

label.value: abolished nuclear pore localization to mitotic nuclear bridge

value.value: A localization phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nuclear pore localization to the portion of the nuclear envelope enclosing the mitotic nuclear bridge does not occur. The nuclear bridge is a narrow constricted region of the nucleus that forms around the mitotic spindle during anaphase. Normally, nuclear pores that lack baskets are found in the midzone of the nuclear bridge.

label.value: abnormal nuclear envelope morphology at mitotic nuclear bridge

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of the portion of the nuclear envelope enclosing the mitotic nuclear bridge is abnormal. The nuclear bridge is a narrow constricted region of the nucleus that forms around the mitotic spindle during anaphase.

label.value: abnormal nuclear envelope morphology at mitotic nuclear bridge midzone

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the size, shape, or structure of the portion of the nuclear envelope enclosing the midzone of the mitotic nuclear bridge is abnormal. The nuclear bridge is a narrow constricted region of the nucleus that forms around the mitotic spindle during anaphase.

label.value: sensitive to histidine

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to histidine. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of histidine that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased filamentous actin level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of filamentous actin measured the cell is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. The total actin level (globular and filamentous actin) may be normal or abnormal.

label.value: normal transcription termination

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the termination of RNA transcription from a DNA template is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased RNA level during cellular response to hypoxia

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to hypoxia is higher than normal. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

label.value: altered spatial extent of protein localization to chromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a protein localizes to chromatin over a different spatial extent than normal. The protein may localize to a larger or smaller region than normal, or its localization may be shifted along the length of the chromosome.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal histone H3-K9 methylation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 is abnormal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 methylation during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal during G0 phase.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 dimethylation during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which dimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal during G0 phase.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 trimethylation during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which methylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 occurs to a greater extent than normal during G0 phase.

label.value: abnormal histone modification during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype that affects histone modification during G0 phase.

label.value: abnormal heterochromatin organization during G0

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which any process of heterochromatin organization is abnormal during G0 phase. Heterochromatin organization results in the specification, formation or maintenance of the physical structure of eukaryotic heterochromatin, a compact and highly condensed form of chromatin.
abnormal histone turnover

A cellular process phenotype in which histone exchange is abnormal. Histone exchange is replacement, within chromatin, of resident histones or histone subunits with alternative, sometimes variant, histones or subunits.
decreased histone turnover during G0

A cellular process phenotype in which histone exchange is abnormal during G0 phase. Histone exchange is replacement, within chromatin, of resident histones or histone subunits with alternative, sometimes variant, histones or subunits.

label.value: variable cell size at division

value.value: A cell population phenotype in which cells in a population do not divide at a uniform size, although each cell divides to form equal-size daughter cells. Within one population, some cells may be larger and others smaller than normal (i.e. compared to wild-type cells under the same conditions).

label.value: delayed onset of protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body begins later than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased duration of cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of an otherwise normal occurrence of cell cycle arrest in mitotic G1 phase is shorter than normal.

label.value: abnormal epigenetic heterochromatin inheritance

value.value: A phenotype in which the stable inheritance of heterochromatic structure is abnormal in regions of the genome where heterochromatin is normally maintained over successive generations.

label.value: decreased epigenetic heterochromatin inheritance

value.value: A phenotype in which a region of the genome that is normally stably assembled and maintained as heterochromatin over successive generations retains heterochromatic structure for fewer generations than normal.

label.value: normal epigenetic heterochromatin inheritance

value.value: A phenotype in which the assembly and stable inheritance of heterochromatic structure is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in regions of the genome where heterochromatin is normally maintained over successive generations.

label.value: decreased spatial extent of subtelomeric heterochromatin assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which heterochromatin is assembled over a smaller portion of the subtelomeric region of the chromosome than normal.

label.value: attenuated increase in transcription during cellular response to stress in presence of small molecule

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which an increase in the transcription of one or more target genes that would normally occur when cells are subjected to a stress in the presence of a specific small molecule occurs to a lower extent than normal under the same circumstances.

label.value: decreased protein localization to meiotic spindle pole body during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle pole body is decreased during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal meiotic spindle pole body duplication during meiosis I

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which meiotic spindle pole body duplication is abnormal during the first meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: abnormal microtubule nucleation

value.value: A microtubule cytoskeleton organization phenotype in which nucleation of microtubules from one or more microtubule organizing centers (MTOCs) is abnormal.

label.value: abolished meiotic spindle microtubule nucleation from new spindle pole body during meiosis II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which nucleation of spindle microtubules from the new spindle pole body does not occur during the second meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: monopolar spindle during meiosis II

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype in which the spindle forms with microtubules emanating from only one pole during the second meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: abolished new meiotic spindle pole body insertion into nuclear envelope during meiosis II

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which insertion of the newly formed spindle pole body into the nuclear envelope does not occur during the second meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: decreased protein localization to Golgi apparatus, with protein mislocalized to vacuole

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the Golgi apparatus is decreased, and the protein is present in the vacuole instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to Golgi apparatus, with protein mislocalized to cytosol

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the Golgi apparatus is decreased, and the protein is present in the cytosol instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal mannosyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a mannosyltransferase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal O-linked glycoprotein glycan structure

value.value: A phenotype in which the structure of an O-linked glycan moiety of a nascent or mature glycoprotein is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: altered level of substance in cell wall

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of a specific substance measured in the cell wall differs from normal.

label.value: decreased ascospore wall alpha-glucan level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of alpha-D-glucan measured in the spore wall is lower than normal.

label.value: increased ascospore wall beta-glucan level

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of beta-D-glucan measured in the spore wall is higher than normal.

label.value: normal protein localization to Mei2 nuclear dot

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the Mei2 nuclear dot is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). The Mei2 nuclear dot is a nuclear body that contains Mei2, other proteins, and meiRNA, and forms during meiotic prophase in a fixed position in the horsetail nucleus.

definition.value: In some mutants, a focus that contains meiRNA but not Mei2 can form; this is called the meiRNA nuclear dot. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nuclear exosome focus at sme2 locus

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nuclear exosome focus at the sme2 locus does not occur. Other nuclear exosome foci may form normally.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: aggregated nuclear exosome foci

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which fewer, larger nuclear exosome foci are present than normal. Nuclear exosome foci, also called Mmi1 foci, are small structures that form within the nucleus, and contain proteins involved in degrading meiosis-specific RNAs during the mitotic cell cycle, such as Mmi1, Iss10, and Red1.

label.value: decreased chromatin binding at cohesin associated regions

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) at one or more cohesin-associated regions (CARs) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene, and may normally bind DNA, protein, or both in chromatin.

label.value: increased chromatin binding at cohesin associated regions

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of chromatin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) at one or more cohesin-associated regions (CARs) in a mutant is increased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene, and may normally bind DNA, protein, or both in chromatin.

label.value: abolished macroautophagy during sulfur starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which macroautophagy does not occur when the cell is subject to sulfur starvation.
